		<div class="post" id="post-2811750">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2811750)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2811750">
																		Co-Author Post
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183505" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1493999665 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">05 May 2017 15:54</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2811750">
									

<p>Firstly, allow me to thank Solo for starting this thing and allowing me to basically expand upon IJAMEA. This is my first collab, and I am only honoured to have partaken in it to the very end.</p>
<p>Speaking as a RL Japanese Studies minor (in progress), it was an absolute honour to have written all of that down.</p>
<p>It is often said that the Japanese like to integrate the culture of others and make it theirs, from Chinese characters to Western technology. After all, Wakon-kansai (和魂漢才 &quot;Japanese spirit and Chinese scholarship&quot;) and Wakon-yōsai (和魂洋才 &quot;Japanese spirit and Western techniques&quot;) are cultural phenomena.</p>
<p>IJAMEA would be no more different, bringing a Western exterior to the Japanese paranormal scene. They will grow and adapt to whatever that works. If something can shake the America that ended Imperial Japan, why not learn from it?</p>
<p>Shushu-in and Unit Negative Numbers are GoIs from the Japanese site (more information in English available <a href="http://scp-int.wikidot.com/jp-goi-hub">here</a>). Since <a href="https://twitter.com/Chysophylax/status/819182774665916416">a significant number of users</a> from the JP site think that all parties can co-exist, I suppose a brief mention would be in order.</p>
<p>Thank you to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fumeinadebaisu" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2831477); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2831477&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1493999825" alt="fumeinadebaisu" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2831477)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/fumeinadebaisu" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2831477); return false;">fumeinadebaisu</a></span> for bringing the poll up.</p>

							</div>

								
